\ In-place reversal through the general strided slice!: source and target the
\ same array, step -1, ends aligned ( arr offset n -- arr ).

: rev! | >arr >off >n |
  arr off  arr off n f+ f1-  -1 n slice! ;

variable nums

[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to nums   nums 0 5 rev! drop   nums . cr   \ [ 5 4 3 2 1 ]
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to nums   nums 0 3 rev! drop   nums . cr   \ [ 3 2 1 4 5 ]
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to nums   nums 1 3 rev! drop   nums . cr   \ [ 1 4 3 2 5 ]
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to nums   nums 2 1 rev! drop   nums . cr   \ single element, unchanged
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to nums   nums 2 0 rev! drop   nums . cr   \ empty slice, unchanged
[ 9 ] to nums   nums 0 1 rev! drop   nums . cr           \ [ 9 ]

\ it leaves the array, so it chains
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 5 rev! . cr                     \ [ 5 4 3 2 1 ]

\ errors
[ 1 2 3 ] 0 5 rev!     \ slice past the end
[ 1 2 3 ] 2 2 rev!     \ offset + n past the end
[ 1 2 3 ] -1 2 rev!    \ negative offset
[ 1 2 3 ] 0 -1 rev!    \ negative count
5 0 1 rev!             \ not an array
